<header class="page-head"><p class="eyebrow">Interpretation with visible seams</p><h1>Article Lab</h1><p class="lede">The Lab treats the body text and its annotations as speakers in a deliberate conversation. It records what the tension may prevent, what research supports or challenges the claim, and where evidence is still absent. It does not rewrite the canon or claim edcmbone measurement status.</p></header>
<div class="grid">{% for unit in generated.canon.units %}<a class="card" href="/lab/{{ unit.id | slug }}/"><span class="status status-interpretation">Lab</span><h2>{{ unit.title }}</h2><p>{{ unit.notes.length }} separately parsed note{% if unit.notes.length != 1 %}s{% endif %} · source lines {{ unit.startLine }}–{{ unit.endLine }}</p></a>{% endfor %}</div>
<section class="hmmm"><h2>Research coverage</h2><p>The Lab route exists for every discovered canonical unit. Reviewed support, dissent, mixed evidence, and synthesis are intentionally published unit by unit rather than mass-invented.</p></section>
